      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Grok web billing status 7 auth and cookie bearer fetch",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Treat gRPC status **7** OAuth2 `bad-credentials` responses as auth failures (in addition to status 16)\n- Try **browser cookies + bearer token** before cookie-only when fetching Grok web billing\n- Skip expired `~/.grok/auth.json` bearer-only fallback after cookie import fails\n- Parse **unframed protobuf** billing payloads when gRPC-web framing is absent\n- Surface clearer grok.com reauth guidance in RPC errors and the Grok menu error state\n\n## Problem\n\nGrok web billing could fail with `RPC failed with status 7` even when:\n- the user was signed into grok.com in Chrome, and/or\n- `~/.grok/auth.json` contained a non-expired token\n\nIn practice, grok.com billing often needs the browser session cookie together with a bearer token, and some successful responses arrive as raw protobuf instead of gRPC-web frames.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `swift test --filter GrokWebBillingFetcherTests`\n- [x] `swift test --filter GrokAuthTests`\n- [x] `swift test --filter CodexUserFacingErrorTests`\n- [x] `make check`",
